♪What we had may be old♪

249
00:15:40,190 --> 00:15:43,430
♪But this longing still feels fresh♪

250
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:49,270
♪How do I even ask you to stay?♪

251
00:15:50,800 --> 00:15:57,200
♪What about the laughter
we once shared?♪

252
00:15:57,890 --> 00:16:04,380
♪How long has it been
since we first met?♪

253
00:16:04,590 --> 00:16:12,739
♪Somehow, the blue sky
has turned gray again♪

254
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:15,829
♪This foolish self-deception♪

255
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:19,489
♪How can excuses ever mend the pain?♪

256
00:16:19,490 --> 00:16:22,850
♪Love is silence♪

257
00:16:23,140 --> 00:16:26,129
♪Love is helplessness♪

258
00:16:26,130 --> 00:16:30,519
♪Love is a pair of eyes
gazing at the stars♪

259
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:33,789
♪Quietly shining for you♪

260
00:16:33,790 --> 00:16:37,449
♪Love is silence♪

261
00:16:37,450 --> 00:16:40,929
♪Love is holding on♪

262
00:16:40,930 --> 00:16:47,440
♪Even if I still cling
to a senseless hope♪
